<paragraph id="D4109BD11639975F4FBB60AAFDCD0C77" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0605E41BAD0B9026CCEF965284D77EEB" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<bibRefCitation id="23861BC70AA076B9D0FDE82C49F51DE6" author="Dahlbom, AG" journalOrPublisher="Nicolai, Berlin" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" title="Hymenoptera Europaea praecipue Borealia, formis typicis nonnullis, specierum generumve exoticorum propter nexum systematicum associatis, per familias, genera, species et varietates disposita atque descripta ab Adrea Gustavo Dahlbom. Chrysis in sensu Linneano" year="1854">Dahlbom (1854</bibRefCitation>
: 49) described 
<taxonomicName id="0DA55E821DE5DDFBB4705B22C390AAE3" authority="Dahlbom, 1854" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1854" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Holopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Holopyga luzulina" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luzulina">Holopyga luzulina</taxonomicName>
based on two specimens received from Milde and Spinola. French labelled the specimen in the Spinola collection as lectotype, but the designation has not been published. Since we could not find the second syntype in MNHU, we designate the lectotype of 
<taxonomicName id="0F9225E7E1ED10B16845A49C4FC9AD33" authority="Dahlbom, 1854" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1854" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Holopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Holopyga luzulina" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luzulina">Holopyga luzulina</taxonomicName>
Dahlbom to fix the current interpretation of the species. After Dahlbom, many South American 
<taxonomicName id="806242B4BEFE333A233A412C65788E95" authority="Dahlbom, 1854" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1854" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Holopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Holopyga" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Holopyga</taxonomicName>
have been described, and there is the possibility that the other syntype belongs to a different species, as found in other cases (e.g. 
<taxonomicName id="14ABB509FF3B9DABE53455133DA49A35" authority="Dahlbom, 1854" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1854" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Holopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Holopyga dohrni" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dohrni">Holopyga dohrni</taxonomicName>
Dahlbom, 1854, with different syntypes from U.S.A. and Cuba). The type is missing tibia and tarsi of the right foreleg and left mesoleg and also the femora, tibiae, and tarsi of the left metaleg; a thin mould layer covers the right side of the body. The second specimen placed under the name 
<taxonomicName id="ABF6F2F8FE4D50606AFDD7B6B76B75F9" authority="Dahlbom, 1854" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1854" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Holopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Holopyga luzulina" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luzulina">Holopyga luzulina</taxonomicName>
is a male of 
<taxonomicName id="E1EAAEAC6E6641A9E562A4E6F14F345C" authority="Latreille, 1802" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Hedychrum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hedychrum rutilans" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rutilans">Hedychrum rutilans</taxonomicName>
Dahlbom, 1854, most likely placed in this position in recent times.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
